34namespace webrtc {

36namespace {
37// From RTCPSender video report interval.
38constexpr TimeDelta kLossUpdateInterval = TimeDelta::Millis(1000);
39
40// Pacing-rate relative to our target send rate.
41// Multiplicative factor that is applied to the target bitrate to calculate
42// the number of bytes that can be transmitted per interval.
43// Increasing this factor will result in lower delays in cases of bitrate
44// overshoots from the encoder.
45constexpr float kDefaultPaceMultiplier = 2.5f;
46
47// If the probe result is far below the current throughput estimate
48// it's unlikely that the probe is accurate, so we don't want to drop too far.
49// However, if we actually are overusing, we want to drop to something slightly
50// below the current throughput estimate to drain the network queues.
51constexpr double kProbeDropThroughputFraction = 0.85;
52
53int64_t GetBpsOrDefault(const absl::optional<DataRate>& rate,
54 int64_t fallback_bps) {
55 if (rate && rate->IsFinite()) {
56 return rate->bps();
57 } else {
58 return fallback_bps;
59 }
60}
61
62bool IsEnabled(const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* config, absl::string_view key) {
63 return absl::StartsWith(config->Lookup(key), "Enabled");
64}
65
66bool IsNotDisabled(const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* config, absl::string_view key) {
67 return !absl::StartsWith(config->Lookup(key), "Disabled");
68}

71GoogCcNetworkController::GoogCcNetworkController(NetworkControllerConfig config,
72 GoogCcConfig goog_cc_config)
73 : key_value_config_(config.key_value_config ? config.key_value_config
74 : &trial_based_config_),
75 event_log_(config.event_log),
76 packet_feedback_only_(goog_cc_config.feedback_only),
77 safe_reset_on_route_change_("Enabled"),
78 safe_reset_acknowledged_rate_("ack"),
79 use_min_allocatable_as_lower_bound_(
80 IsNotDisabled(key_value_config_, "WebRTC-Bwe-MinAllocAsLowerBound")),
81 ignore_probes_lower_than_network_estimate_(IsNotDisabled(
82 key_value_config_,
83 "WebRTC-Bwe-IgnoreProbesLowerThanNetworkStateEstimate")),
84 limit_probes_lower_than_throughput_estimate_(
85 IsEnabled(key_value_config_,
86 "WebRTC-Bwe-LimitProbesLowerThanThroughputEstimate")),
87 rate_control_settings_(
88 RateControlSettings::ParseFromKeyValueConfig(key_value_config_)),
89 loss_based_stable_rate_(
90 IsEnabled(key_value_config_, "WebRTC-Bwe-LossBasedStableRate")),
91 probe_controller_(
92 new ProbeController(key_value_config_, config.event_log)),
93 congestion_window_pushback_controller_(
94 rate_control_settings_.UseCongestionWindowPushback()
95 ? std::make_unique<CongestionWindowPushbackController>(
96 key_value_config_)
97 : nullptr),
98 bandwidth_estimation_(
99 std::make_unique<SendSideBandwidthEstimation>(key_value_config_,
100 event_log_)),
101 alr_detector_(
102 std::make_unique<AlrDetector>(key_value_config_, config.event_log)),
103 probe_bitrate_estimator_(new ProbeBitrateEstimator(config.event_log)),
104 network_estimator_(std::move(goog_cc_config.network_state_estimator)),
105 network_state_predictor_(
106 std::move(goog_cc_config.network_state_predictor)),
107 delay_based_bwe_(new DelayBasedBwe(key_value_config_,
108 event_log_,
109 network_state_predictor_.get())),
110 acknowledged_bitrate_estimator_(
111 AcknowledgedBitrateEstimatorInterface::Create(key_value_config_)),
112 initial_config_(config),
113 last_loss_based_target_rate_(*config.constraints.starting_rate),
114 last_pushback_target_rate_(last_loss_based_target_rate_),
115 last_stable_target_rate_(last_loss_based_target_rate_),
116 pacing_factor_(config.stream_based_config.pacing_factor.value_or(
117 kDefaultPaceMultiplier)),
118 min_total_allocated_bitrate_(
119 config.stream_based_config.min_total_allocated_bitrate.value_or(
120 DataRate::Zero())),
121 max_padding_rate_(config.stream_based_config.max_padding_rate.value_or(
122 DataRate::Zero())),
123 max_total_allocated_bitrate_(DataRate::Zero()) {
124 RTC_DCHECK(config.constraints.at_time.IsFinite());
125 ParseFieldTrial(
126 {&safe_reset_on_route_change_, &safe_reset_acknowledged_rate_},
127 key_value_config_->Lookup("WebRTC-Bwe-SafeResetOnRouteChange"));
128 if (delay_based_bwe_)
129 delay_based_bwe_->SetMinBitrate(congestion_controller::GetMinBitrate());
130}
131
132GoogCcNetworkController::~GoogCcNetworkController() {}
133
134NetworkControlUpdate GoogCcNetworkController::OnNetworkAvailability(
135 NetworkAvailability msg) {
136 NetworkControlUpdate update;
137 update.probe_cluster_configs = probe_controller_->OnNetworkAvailability(msg);
138 return update;
139}
140
141NetworkControlUpdate GoogCcNetworkController::OnNetworkRouteChange(
142 NetworkRouteChange msg) {
143 if (safe_reset_on_route_change_) {
144 absl::optional<DataRate> estimated_bitrate;
145 if (safe_reset_acknowledged_rate_) {
146 estimated_bitrate = acknowledged_bitrate_estimator_->bitrate();
147 if (!estimated_bitrate)
148 estimated_bitrate = acknowledged_bitrate_estimator_->PeekRate();
149 } else {
150 estimated_bitrate = bandwidth_estimation_->target_rate();
151 }
152 if (estimated_bitrate) {
153 if (msg.constraints.starting_rate) {
154 msg.constraints.starting_rate =
155 std::min(*msg.constraints.starting_rate, *estimated_bitrate);
156 } else {
157 msg.constraints.starting_rate = estimated_bitrate;
158 }
159 }
160 }
161
162 acknowledged_bitrate_estimator_ =
163 AcknowledgedBitrateEstimatorInterface::Create(key_value_config_);
164 probe_bitrate_estimator_.reset(new ProbeBitrateEstimator(event_log_));
165 if (network_estimator_)
166 network_estimator_->OnRouteChange(msg);
167 delay_based_bwe_.reset(new DelayBasedBwe(key_value_config_, event_log_,
168 network_state_predictor_.get()));
169 bandwidth_estimation_->OnRouteChange();
170 probe_controller_->Reset(msg.at_time.ms());
171 NetworkControlUpdate update;
172 update.probe_cluster_configs = ResetConstraints(msg.constraints);
173 MaybeTriggerOnNetworkChanged(&update, msg.at_time);
174 return update;
175}
176
177NetworkControlUpdate GoogCcNetworkController::OnProcessInterval(
178 ProcessInterval msg) {
179 NetworkControlUpdate update;
180 if (initial_config_) {
181 update.probe_cluster_configs =
182 ResetConstraints(initial_config_->constraints);
183 update.pacer_config = GetPacingRates(msg.at_time);
184
185 if (initial_config_->stream_based_config.requests_alr_probing) {
186 probe_controller_->EnablePeriodicAlrProbing(
187 *initial_config_->stream_based_config.requests_alr_probing);
188 }
189 absl::optional<DataRate> total_bitrate =
190 initial_config_->stream_based_config.max_total_allocated_bitrate;
191 if (total_bitrate) {
192 auto probes = probe_controller_->OnMaxTotalAllocatedBitrate(
193 total_bitrate->bps(), msg.at_time.ms());
194 update.probe_cluster_configs.insert(update.probe_cluster_configs.end(),
195 probes.begin(), probes.end());
196
197 max_total_allocated_bitrate_ = *total_bitrate;
198 }
199 initial_config_.reset();
200 }
201 if (congestion_window_pushback_controller_ && msg.pacer_queue) {
202 congestion_window_pushback_controller_->UpdatePacingQueue(
203 msg.pacer_queue->bytes());
204 }
205 bandwidth_estimation_->UpdateEstimate(msg.at_time);
206 absl::optional<int64_t> start_time_ms =
207 alr_detector_->GetApplicationLimitedRegionStartTime();
208 probe_controller_->SetAlrStartTimeMs(start_time_ms);
209
210 auto probes = probe_controller_->Process(msg.at_time.ms());
211 update.probe_cluster_configs.insert(update.probe_cluster_configs.end(),
212 probes.begin(), probes.end());
213
214 if (rate_control_settings_.UseCongestionWindow() &&
215 last_packet_received_time_.IsFinite() && !feedback_max_rtts_.empty()) {
216 UpdateCongestionWindowSize();
217 }
218 if (congestion_window_pushback_controller_ && current_data_window_) {
219 congestion_window_pushback_controller_->SetDataWindow(
220 *current_data_window_);
221 } else {
222 update.congestion_window = current_data_window_;
223 }
224 MaybeTriggerOnNetworkChanged(&update, msg.at_time);
225 return update;
226}
227
228NetworkControlUpdate GoogCcNetworkController::OnRemoteBitrateReport(
229 RemoteBitrateReport msg) {
230 if (packet_feedback_only_) {
231 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Received REMB for packet feedback only GoogCC";
232 return NetworkControlUpdate();
233 }
234 bandwidth_estimation_->UpdateReceiverEstimate(msg.receive_time,
235 msg.bandwidth);
236 BWE_TEST_LOGGING_PLOT(1, "REMB_kbps", msg.receive_time.ms(),
237 msg.bandwidth.bps() / 1000);
238 return NetworkControlUpdate();
239}
240
241NetworkControlUpdate GoogCcNetworkController::OnRoundTripTimeUpdate(
242 RoundTripTimeUpdate msg) {
243 if (packet_feedback_only_ || msg.smoothed)
244 return NetworkControlUpdate();
245 RTC_DCHECK(!msg.round_trip_time.IsZero());
246 if (delay_based_bwe_)
247 delay_based_bwe_->OnRttUpdate(msg.round_trip_time);
248 bandwidth_estimation_->UpdateRtt(msg.round_trip_time, msg.receive_time);
249 return NetworkControlUpdate();
250}
251
252NetworkControlUpdate GoogCcNetworkController::OnSentPacket(
253 SentPacket sent_packet) {
254 alr_detector_->OnBytesSent(sent_packet.size.bytes(),
255 sent_packet.send_time.ms());
256 acknowledged_bitrate_estimator_->SetAlr(
257 alr_detector_->GetApplicationLimitedRegionStartTime().has_value());
258
259 if (!first_packet_sent_) {
260 first_packet_sent_ = true;
261 // Initialize feedback time to send time to allow estimation of RTT until
262 // first feedback is received.
263 bandwidth_estimation_->UpdatePropagationRtt(sent_packet.send_time,
264 TimeDelta::Zero());
265 }
266 bandwidth_estimation_->OnSentPacket(sent_packet);
267
268 if (congestion_window_pushback_controller_) {
269 congestion_window_pushback_controller_->UpdateOutstandingData(
270 sent_packet.data_in_flight.bytes());
271 NetworkControlUpdate update;
272 MaybeTriggerOnNetworkChanged(&update, sent_packet.send_time);
273 return update;
274 } else {
275 return NetworkControlUpdate();
276 }
277}
278
279NetworkControlUpdate GoogCcNetworkController::OnReceivedPacket(
280 ReceivedPacket received_packet) {
281 last_packet_received_time_ = received_packet.receive_time;
282 return NetworkControlUpdate();
283}
284
285NetworkControlUpdate GoogCcNetworkController::OnStreamsConfig(
286 StreamsConfig msg) {
287 NetworkControlUpdate update;
288 if (msg.requests_alr_probing) {
289 probe_controller_->EnablePeriodicAlrProbing(*msg.requests_alr_probing);
290 }
291 if (msg.max_total_allocated_bitrate &&
292 *msg.max_total_allocated_bitrate != max_total_allocated_bitrate_) {
293 if (rate_control_settings_.TriggerProbeOnMaxAllocatedBitrateChange()) {
294 update.probe_cluster_configs =
295 probe_controller_->OnMaxTotalAllocatedBitrate(
296 msg.max_total_allocated_bitrate->bps(), msg.at_time.ms());
297 } else {
298 probe_controller_->SetMaxBitrate(msg.max_total_allocated_bitrate->bps());
299 }
300 max_total_allocated_bitrate_ = *msg.max_total_allocated_bitrate;
301 }
302 bool pacing_changed = false;
303 if (msg.pacing_factor && *msg.pacing_factor != pacing_factor_) {
304 pacing_factor_ = *msg.pacing_factor;
305 pacing_changed = true;
306 }
307 if (msg.min_total_allocated_bitrate &&
308 *msg.min_total_allocated_bitrate != min_total_allocated_bitrate_) {
309 min_total_allocated_bitrate_ = *msg.min_total_allocated_bitrate;
310 pacing_changed = true;
311
312 if (use_min_allocatable_as_lower_bound_) {
313 ClampConstraints();
314 delay_based_bwe_->SetMinBitrate(min_data_rate_);
315 bandwidth_estimation_->SetMinMaxBitrate(min_data_rate_, max_data_rate_);
316 }
317 }
318 if (msg.max_padding_rate && *msg.max_padding_rate != max_padding_rate_) {
319 max_padding_rate_ = *msg.max_padding_rate;
320 pacing_changed = true;
321 }
322
323 if (pacing_changed)
324 update.pacer_config = GetPacingRates(msg.at_time);
325 return update;
326}
327
328NetworkControlUpdate GoogCcNetworkController::OnTargetRateConstraints(
329 TargetRateConstraints constraints) {
330 NetworkControlUpdate update;
331 update.probe_cluster_configs = ResetConstraints(constraints);
332 MaybeTriggerOnNetworkChanged(&update, constraints.at_time);
333 return update;
334}
335
336void GoogCcNetworkController::ClampConstraints() {
337 // TODO(holmer): We should make sure the default bitrates are set to 10 kbps,
338 // and that we don't try to set the min bitrate to 0 from any applications.
339 // The congestion controller should allow a min bitrate of 0.
340 min_data_rate_ =
341 std::max(min_target_rate_, congestion_controller::GetMinBitrate());
342 if (use_min_allocatable_as_lower_bound_) {
343 min_data_rate_ = std::max(min_data_rate_, min_total_allocated_bitrate_);
344 }
345 if (max_data_rate_ < min_data_rate_) {
346 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "max bitrate smaller than min bitrate";
347 max_data_rate_ = min_data_rate_;
348 }
349 if (starting_rate_ && starting_rate_ < min_data_rate_) {
350 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "start bitrate smaller than min bitrate";
351 starting_rate_ = min_data_rate_;
352 }
353}
354
355std::vector<ProbeClusterConfig> GoogCcNetworkController::ResetConstraints(
356 TargetRateConstraints new_constraints) {
357 min_target_rate_ = new_constraints.min_data_rate.value_or(DataRate::Zero());
358 max_data_rate_ =
359 new_constraints.max_data_rate.value_or(DataRate::PlusInfinity());
360 starting_rate_ = new_constraints.starting_rate;
361 ClampConstraints();
362
363 bandwidth_estimation_->SetBitrates(starting_rate_, min_data_rate_,
364 max_data_rate_, new_constraints.at_time);
365
366 if (starting_rate_)
367 delay_based_bwe_->SetStartBitrate(*starting_rate_);
368 delay_based_bwe_->SetMinBitrate(min_data_rate_);
369
370 return probe_controller_->SetBitrates(
371 min_data_rate_.bps(), GetBpsOrDefault(starting_rate_, -1),
372 max_data_rate_.bps_or(-1), new_constraints.at_time.ms());
373}
374
375NetworkControlUpdate GoogCcNetworkController::OnTransportLossReport(
376 TransportLossReport msg) {
377 if (packet_feedback_only_)
378 return NetworkControlUpdate();
379 int64_t total_packets_delta =
380 msg.packets_received_delta + msg.packets_lost_delta;
381 bandwidth_estimation_->UpdatePacketsLost(
382 msg.packets_lost_delta, total_packets_delta, msg.receive_time);
383 return NetworkControlUpdate();
384}
385
386void GoogCcNetworkController::UpdateCongestionWindowSize() {
387 TimeDelta min_feedback_max_rtt = TimeDelta::Millis(
388 *std::min_element(feedback_max_rtts_.begin(), feedback_max_rtts_.end()));
389
390 const DataSize kMinCwnd = DataSize::Bytes(2 * 1500);
391 TimeDelta time_window =
392 min_feedback_max_rtt +
393 TimeDelta::Millis(
394 rate_control_settings_.GetCongestionWindowAdditionalTimeMs());
395
396 DataSize data_window = last_loss_based_target_rate_ * time_window;
397 if (current_data_window_) {
398 data_window =
399 std::max(kMinCwnd, (data_window + current_data_window_.value()) / 2);
400 } else {
401 data_window = std::max(kMinCwnd, data_window);
402 }
403 current_data_window_ = data_window;
404}
405
406NetworkControlUpdate GoogCcNetworkController::OnTransportPacketsFeedback(
407 TransportPacketsFeedback report) {
408 if (report.packet_feedbacks.empty()) {
409 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10125): Design a better mechanism to safe-guard
410 // against building very large network queues.
411 return NetworkControlUpdate();
412 }
413
414 if (congestion_window_pushback_controller_) {
415 congestion_window_pushback_controller_->UpdateOutstandingData(
416 report.data_in_flight.bytes());
417 }
418 TimeDelta max_feedback_rtt = TimeDelta::MinusInfinity();
419 TimeDelta min_propagation_rtt = TimeDelta::PlusInfinity();
420 Timestamp max_recv_time = Timestamp::MinusInfinity();
421
422 std::vector<PacketResult> feedbacks = report.ReceivedWithSendInfo();
423 for (const auto& feedback : feedbacks)
424 max_recv_time = std::max(max_recv_time, feedback.receive_time);
425
426 for (const auto& feedback : feedbacks) {
427 TimeDelta feedback_rtt =
428 report.feedback_time - feedback.sent_packet.send_time;
429 TimeDelta min_pending_time = feedback.receive_time - max_recv_time;
430 TimeDelta propagation_rtt = feedback_rtt - min_pending_time;
431 max_feedback_rtt = std::max(max_feedback_rtt, feedback_rtt);
432 min_propagation_rtt = std::min(min_propagation_rtt, propagation_rtt);
433 }
434
435 if (max_feedback_rtt.IsFinite()) {
436 feedback_max_rtts_.push_back(max_feedback_rtt.ms());
437 const size_t kMaxFeedbackRttWindow = 32;
438 if (feedback_max_rtts_.size() > kMaxFeedbackRttWindow)
439 feedback_max_rtts_.pop_front();
440 // TODO(srte): Use time since last unacknowledged packet.
441 bandwidth_estimation_->UpdatePropagationRtt(report.feedback_time,
442 min_propagation_rtt);
443 }
444 if (packet_feedback_only_) {
445 if (!feedback_max_rtts_.empty()) {
446 int64_t sum_rtt_ms = std::accumulate(feedback_max_rtts_.begin(),
447 feedback_max_rtts_.end(), 0);
448 int64_t mean_rtt_ms = sum_rtt_ms / feedback_max_rtts_.size();
449 if (delay_based_bwe_)
450 delay_based_bwe_->OnRttUpdate(TimeDelta::Millis(mean_rtt_ms));
451 }
452
453 TimeDelta feedback_min_rtt = TimeDelta::PlusInfinity();
454 for (const auto& packet_feedback : feedbacks) {
455 TimeDelta pending_time = packet_feedback.receive_time - max_recv_time;
456 TimeDelta rtt = report.feedback_time -
457 packet_feedback.sent_packet.send_time - pending_time;
458 // Value used for predicting NACK round trip time in FEC controller.
459 feedback_min_rtt = std::min(rtt, feedback_min_rtt);
460 }
461 if (feedback_min_rtt.IsFinite()) {
462 bandwidth_estimation_->UpdateRtt(feedback_min_rtt, report.feedback_time);
463 }
464
465 expected_packets_since_last_loss_update_ +=
466 report.PacketsWithFeedback().size();
467 for (const auto& packet_feedback : report.PacketsWithFeedback()) {
468 if (packet_feedback.receive_time.IsInfinite())
469 lost_packets_since_last_loss_update_ += 1;
470 }
471 if (report.feedback_time > next_loss_update_) {
472 next_loss_update_ = report.feedback_time + kLossUpdateInterval;
473 bandwidth_estimation_->UpdatePacketsLost(
474 lost_packets_since_last_loss_update_,
475 expected_packets_since_last_loss_update_, report.feedback_time);
476 expected_packets_since_last_loss_update_ = 0;
477 lost_packets_since_last_loss_update_ = 0;
478 }
479 }
480 absl::optional<int64_t> alr_start_time =
481 alr_detector_->GetApplicationLimitedRegionStartTime();
482
483 if (previously_in_alr_ && !alr_start_time.has_value()) {
484 int64_t now_ms = report.feedback_time.ms();
485 acknowledged_bitrate_estimator_->SetAlrEndedTime(report.feedback_time);
486 probe_controller_->SetAlrEndedTimeMs(now_ms);
487 }
488 previously_in_alr_ = alr_start_time.has_value();
489 acknowledged_bitrate_estimator_->IncomingPacketFeedbackVector(
490 report.SortedByReceiveTime());
491 auto acknowledged_bitrate = acknowledged_bitrate_estimator_->bitrate();
492 bandwidth_estimation_->SetAcknowledgedRate(acknowledged_bitrate,
493 report.feedback_time);
494 bandwidth_estimation_->IncomingPacketFeedbackVector(report);
495 for (const auto& feedback : report.SortedByReceiveTime()) {
496 if (feedback.sent_packet.pacing_info.probe_cluster_id !=
497 PacedPacketInfo::kNotAProbe) {
498 probe_bitrate_estimator_->HandleProbeAndEstimateBitrate(feedback);
499 }
500 }
501
502 if (network_estimator_) {
503 network_estimator_->OnTransportPacketsFeedback(report);
504 auto prev_estimate = estimate_;
505 estimate_ = network_estimator_->GetCurrentEstimate();
506 // TODO(srte): Make OnTransportPacketsFeedback signal whether the state
507 // changed to avoid the need for this check.
508 if (estimate_ && (!prev_estimate || estimate_->last_feed_time !=
509 prev_estimate->last_feed_time)) {
510 event_log_->Log(std::make_unique<RtcEventRemoteEstimate>(
511 estimate_->link_capacity_lower, estimate_->link_capacity_upper));
512 }
513 }
514 absl::optional<DataRate> probe_bitrate =
515 probe_bitrate_estimator_->FetchAndResetLastEstimatedBitrate();
516 if (ignore_probes_lower_than_network_estimate_ && probe_bitrate &&
517 estimate_ && *probe_bitrate < delay_based_bwe_->last_estimate() &&
518 *probe_bitrate < estimate_->link_capacity_lower) {
519 probe_bitrate.reset();
520 }
521 if (limit_probes_lower_than_throughput_estimate_ && probe_bitrate &&
522 acknowledged_bitrate) {
523 // Limit the backoff to something slightly below the acknowledged
524 // bitrate. ("Slightly below" because we want to drain the queues
525 // if we are actually overusing.)
526 // The acknowledged bitrate shouldn't normally be higher than the delay
527 // based estimate, but it could happen e.g. due to packet bursts or
528 // encoder overshoot. We use std::min to ensure that a probe result
529 // below the current BWE never causes an increase.
530 DataRate limit =
531 std::min(delay_based_bwe_->last_estimate(),
532 *acknowledged_bitrate * kProbeDropThroughputFraction);
533 probe_bitrate = std::max(*probe_bitrate, limit);
534 }
535
536 NetworkControlUpdate update;
537 bool recovered_from_overuse = false;
538 bool backoff_in_alr = false;
539
540 DelayBasedBwe::Result result;
541 result = delay_based_bwe_->IncomingPacketFeedbackVector(
542 report, acknowledged_bitrate, probe_bitrate, estimate_,
543 alr_start_time.has_value());
544
545 if (result.updated) {
546 if (result.probe) {
547 bandwidth_estimation_->SetSendBitrate(result.target_bitrate,
548 report.feedback_time);
549 }
550 // Since SetSendBitrate now resets the delay-based estimate, we have to
551 // call UpdateDelayBasedEstimate after SetSendBitrate.
552 bandwidth_estimation_->UpdateDelayBasedEstimate(report.feedback_time,
553 result.target_bitrate);
554 // Update the estimate in the ProbeController, in case we want to probe.
555 MaybeTriggerOnNetworkChanged(&update, report.feedback_time);
556 }
557 recovered_from_overuse = result.recovered_from_overuse;
558 backoff_in_alr = result.backoff_in_alr;
559
560 if (recovered_from_overuse) {
561 probe_controller_->SetAlrStartTimeMs(alr_start_time);
562 auto probes = probe_controller_->RequestProbe(report.feedback_time.ms());
563 update.probe_cluster_configs.insert(update.probe_cluster_configs.end(),
564 probes.begin(), probes.end());
565 } else if (backoff_in_alr) {
566 // If we just backed off during ALR, request a new probe.
567 auto probes = probe_controller_->RequestProbe(report.feedback_time.ms());
568 update.probe_cluster_configs.insert(update.probe_cluster_configs.end(),
569 probes.begin(), probes.end());
570 }
571
572 // No valid RTT could be because send-side BWE isn't used, in which case
573 // we don't try to limit the outstanding packets.
574 if (rate_control_settings_.UseCongestionWindow() &&
575 max_feedback_rtt.IsFinite()) {
576 UpdateCongestionWindowSize();
577 }
578 if (congestion_window_pushback_controller_ && current_data_window_) {
579 congestion_window_pushback_controller_->SetDataWindow(
580 *current_data_window_);
581 } else {
582 update.congestion_window = current_data_window_;
583 }
584
585 return update;
586}

588NetworkControlUpdate GoogCcNetworkController::OnNetworkStateEstimate(
589 NetworkStateEstimate msg) {
590 estimate_ = msg;
591 return NetworkControlUpdate();
592}
593
594NetworkControlUpdate GoogCcNetworkController::GetNetworkState(
595 Timestamp at_time) const {
596 NetworkControlUpdate update;
597 update.target_rate = TargetTransferRate();
598 update.target_rate->network_estimate.at_time = at_time;
599 update.target_rate->network_estimate.loss_rate_ratio =
600 last_estimated_fraction_loss_.value_or(0) / 255.0;
601 update.target_rate->network_estimate.round_trip_time =
602 last_estimated_round_trip_time_;
603 update.target_rate->network_estimate.bwe_period =
604 delay_based_bwe_->GetExpectedBwePeriod();
605
606 update.target_rate->at_time = at_time;
607 update.target_rate->target_rate = last_pushback_target_rate_;
608 update.target_rate->stable_target_rate =
609 bandwidth_estimation_->GetEstimatedLinkCapacity();
610 update.pacer_config = GetPacingRates(at_time);
611 update.congestion_window = current_data_window_;
612 return update;
613}
614
615void GoogCcNetworkController::MaybeTriggerOnNetworkChanged(
616 NetworkControlUpdate* update,
617 Timestamp at_time) {
618 uint8_t fraction_loss = bandwidth_estimation_->fraction_loss();
619 TimeDelta round_trip_time = bandwidth_estimation_->round_trip_time();
620 DataRate loss_based_target_rate = bandwidth_estimation_->target_rate();
621 DataRate pushback_target_rate = loss_based_target_rate;
622
623 BWE_TEST_LOGGING_PLOT(1, "fraction_loss_%", at_time.ms(),
624 (fraction_loss * 100) / 256);
625 BWE_TEST_LOGGING_PLOT(1, "rtt_ms", at_time.ms(), round_trip_time.ms());
626 BWE_TEST_LOGGING_PLOT(1, "Target_bitrate_kbps", at_time.ms(),
627 loss_based_target_rate.kbps());
628
629 double cwnd_reduce_ratio = 0.0;
630 if (congestion_window_pushback_controller_) {
631 int64_t pushback_rate =
632 congestion_window_pushback_controller_->UpdateTargetBitrate(
633 loss_based_target_rate.bps());
634 pushback_rate = std::max<int64_t>(bandwidth_estimation_->GetMinBitrate(),
635 pushback_rate);
636 pushback_target_rate = DataRate::BitsPerSec(pushback_rate);
637 if (rate_control_settings_.UseCongestionWindowDropFrameOnly()) {
638 cwnd_reduce_ratio = static_cast<double>(loss_based_target_rate.bps() -
639 pushback_target_rate.bps()) /
640 loss_based_target_rate.bps();
641 }
642 }
643 DataRate stable_target_rate =
644 bandwidth_estimation_->GetEstimatedLinkCapacity();
645 if (loss_based_stable_rate_) {
646 stable_target_rate = std::min(stable_target_rate, loss_based_target_rate);
647 } else {
648 stable_target_rate = std::min(stable_target_rate, pushback_target_rate);
649 }
650
651 if ((loss_based_target_rate != last_loss_based_target_rate_) ||
652 (fraction_loss != last_estimated_fraction_loss_) ||
653 (round_trip_time != last_estimated_round_trip_time_) ||
654 (pushback_target_rate != last_pushback_target_rate_) ||
655 (stable_target_rate != last_stable_target_rate_)) {
656 last_loss_based_target_rate_ = loss_based_target_rate;
657 last_pushback_target_rate_ = pushback_target_rate;
658 last_estimated_fraction_loss_ = fraction_loss;
659 last_estimated_round_trip_time_ = round_trip_time;
660 last_stable_target_rate_ = stable_target_rate;
661
662 alr_detector_->SetEstimatedBitrate(loss_based_target_rate.bps());
663
664 TimeDelta bwe_period = delay_based_bwe_->GetExpectedBwePeriod();
665
666 TargetTransferRate target_rate_msg;
667 target_rate_msg.at_time = at_time;
668 if (rate_control_settings_.UseCongestionWindowDropFrameOnly()) {
669 target_rate_msg.target_rate = loss_based_target_rate;
670 target_rate_msg.cwnd_reduce_ratio = cwnd_reduce_ratio;
671 } else {
672 target_rate_msg.target_rate = pushback_target_rate;
673 }
674 target_rate_msg.stable_target_rate = stable_target_rate;
675 target_rate_msg.network_estimate.at_time = at_time;
676 target_rate_msg.network_estimate.round_trip_time = round_trip_time;
677 target_rate_msg.network_estimate.loss_rate_ratio = fraction_loss / 255.0f;
678 target_rate_msg.network_estimate.bwe_period = bwe_period;
679
680 update->target_rate = target_rate_msg;
681
682 auto probes = probe_controller_->SetEstimatedBitrate(
683 loss_based_target_rate.bps(), at_time.ms());
684 update->probe_cluster_configs.insert(update->probe_cluster_configs.end(),
685 probes.begin(), probes.end());
686 update->pacer_config = GetPacingRates(at_time);
687
688 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "bwe " << at_time.ms() << " pushback_target_bps="
689 << last_pushback_target_rate_.bps()
690 << " estimate_bps=" << loss_based_target_rate.bps();
691 }
692}
693
694PacerConfig GoogCcNetworkController::GetPacingRates(Timestamp at_time) const {
695 // Pacing rate is based on target rate before congestion window pushback,
696 // because we don't want to build queues in the pacer when pushback occurs.
697 DataRate pacing_rate =
698 std::max(min_total_allocated_bitrate_, last_loss_based_target_rate_) *
699 pacing_factor_;
700 DataRate padding_rate =
701 std::min(max_padding_rate_, last_pushback_target_rate_);
702 PacerConfig msg;
703 msg.at_time = at_time;
704 msg.time_window = TimeDelta::Seconds(1);
705 msg.data_window = pacing_rate * msg.time_window;
706 msg.pad_window = padding_rate * msg.time_window;
707 return msg;
708}
